<subSubSection id="8098C9ADFF84FF816D94F94EF152F906" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C83D9A26FF84FF816D94F94EF152F906" blockId="3.[151,1437,1487,2034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="FAF64634FF84FF816D94F94EF116F96D" bold="true" box="[151,295,1687,1713]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="FAF64634FF84FF816E3FF941F399F96D" box="[828,936,1688,1713]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">
<taxonomicName id="0F82E1A5FF84FF816E3FF941F3B4F96D" box="[828,901,1688,1713]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Platocoelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">brevis</taxonomicName>
, -e
</emphasis>
, meaning short, referring to the short conductor; adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8098C9ADFF84FF816D94F93EF1CAF88E" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C83D9A26FF84FF816D94F93EF1CAF88E" blockId="3.[151,1437,1487,2034]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="FAF64634FF84FF816D94F93EF128F8DD" bold="true" box="[151,281,1767,1793]" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The male of this new species can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="0F82E1A5FF84FF81690DF931F49FF8DD" box="[1038,1198,1768,1793]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Platocoelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FAF64634FF84FF81690DF931F49FF8DD" box="[1038,1198,1768,1793]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">Platocoelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by its short and wide conductor. The female can be separated from other 
<taxonomicName id="0F82E1A5FF84FF816E7CF8C9F42EF8F5" box="[895,1055,1808,1833]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Platocoelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FAF64634FF84FF816E7CF8C9F42EF8F5" box="[895,1055,1808,1833]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="51">Platocoelotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by its simple, globular, closely situated spermathecae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
